         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ Sir.—Herewith you will receive three small packets of seed of three bamboos, ¶ It is probable that the three species implied are those listed underArundinaria falcata, inB76.12.04, where M give...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.09.00h</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Dickinson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's letter not found. The text used here is from 'Hardy bamboos', a letter 'To the EDITOR',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Geelong advertiser</seg>, 17 September 1879, p. 3. The item is dated to September on the assumption that Dickinson would have written to the newspaper soon after receiving the package from M.</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sir.—Herewith you will receive three small packets of seed of three bamboos,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is probable that the three species implied are those listed under<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Arundinaria falcata</seg>, in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">B76.12.04, where M gives the common names 'Ringal or Ningala Bamboo'. It is not known whence M received the seed, but also in 1879 he sent seed of an unknown species to William Woolls in Sydney; see W. Woolls to M, 10 May 1879.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteSymbol" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">kindly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>supplied<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to me by Baron Von Müller. They are a recent arrival from the Himalaya mountains, where they occur in dense thickets, growing upwards of eighty feet in height, …]</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The item continues, offering readers the 'few packets' Dickinson has to spare, commenting on horticultural needs and uses of the plant, as well as referring readers to B76.12.04.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
